<div id="aboutBox" class="Box">
<div class="Box-header">
Quran in Easy to Read English
<a class="Box-close" href="#"></a></div>
<div class="Box-body about-box">
<p>Quran in Today's English. Clear and Easy to Read. Translated by <a href="http://blog.clearquran.com/bio/">Talal Itani.</a></p>
<p>"This Quran could not have been produced by anyone other than God. In fact, it is a confirmation of what preceded it, and an elaboration of the Book. There is no doubt about it-it is from the Lord of the Universe." [Chapter 10, Verse 37]</p>
<p>Talal Itani is an Electronics Engineer. He first read the Quran 1992, out of curiosity. Since then, Talal has been studying the Quran, researching it, and educating others about it.</p>
<p>Talal decided to translate the Quran when he gave up all hope of finding an English Translation that was at the same time highly accurate and very easy to read.</p>
<p>Reader Testimony: "Dear Sir, I had tried many times to read the Quran in English, but the translations were so difficult to understand, that I gave up. I finally found your translation and it is easy to read and understand. I just wanted to thank you for this." [Shuja Mirza]</p>
<p>The Quran is a Reminder. It contains Mercy and Healing, and it is beyond doubt from the Lord of the Worlds.</p>
<p>"When you read the Quran, seek refuge with God from Satan the outcast. He has no authority over those who believe and trust in their Lord. His authority is only over those who follow him, and those who associate others with Him." [Chapter 16, Verses 98-100]</p>
<p>You are free to share and distribute this translation. ClearQuran is provided under the Creative Commons License. Attribution, NonCommercial, NoDerivs. Available in two editions: Edition (A) uses the word 'Allah' to refer to the Creator. Edition (B) uses the word 'God'.</p>
